name: OLD/app2/app2.R
content:
# app.R — HANIFA PRS (brand styled, units fixed + minor fixes) suppressPackageStartupMessages({ library(shiny) library(readxl); library(dplyr); library(stringr) library(DT); library(writexl); library(readr) library(bslib) }) # ---------------- Brand palette ---------------- hanifa_primary <- "#233A8B" # navy hanifa_accent <- "#F4A020" # amber/gold hanifa_dark <- "#101a46" hanifa_light <- "#f7fafc" # Bootstrap theme (use rem/number, not px) theme <- bs_theme( version = 5, primary = hanifa_primary, secondary = hanifa_accent, "font-size-base" = "1.03rem", "border-radius" = ".75rem", "btn-border-radius" = ".75rem" ) # ---------- Helpers ---------- std_names <- function(x) tolower(gsub("\\s+", "", x)) need_cols_excel <- c("snp","chr","bp","genotype","weight","riskallele") is_missing_like <- function(x) x %in% c("--","II","DD") | is.na(x) trim_ws <- function(x) gsub("^\\s+|\\s+$","",x) dosage_vec <- function(geno, risk){ geno <- toupper(geno); risk <- toupper(risk) out <- rep(NA_real_, length(geno)) valid_risk <- risk %in% c("A","C","G","T") valid_geno <- nchar(geno)==2 & grepl("^[ACGT]{2}$", geno) ok <- valid_risk & valid_geno & !is_missing_like(geno) if(!any(ok)) return(out) a1 <- substr(geno[ok],1,1); a2 <- substr(geno[ok],2,2) out[ok] <- (a1==risk[ok]) + (a2==risk[ok]) as.numeric(out) } # ---------------- UI ---------------- ui <- navbarPage( id = "mainnav", theme = theme, title = div( style = "display:flex;align-items:center;gap:.6rem;", img(src="logo.png", height="34", alt="HANIFA"), tags$span(style=sprintf("font-weight:700;color:%s", hanifa_primary),"HANIFA | Interactive PRS") ), header = tags$head( tags$style(HTML(sprintf(" .navbar { box-shadow:0 4px 18px rgba(0,0,0,.07); } .nav-link, .navbar-brand { font-weight:600; } .welcome-card { border-radius:18px; box-shadow:0 10px 26px rgba(0,0,0,.08); padding:24px; background:#fff; } .soft { background:%s; border-radius:16px; padding:18px; } .note { color:#5b6275; font-size:1.05rem; } h3 { font-size:1.8rem; font-weight:800; color:%s; } h4 { font-size:1.25rem; font-weight:700; } .kpi { font-size:1.0rem; background:#eef2f7; border-radius:14px; padding:8px 12px; display:inline-block; margin:4px 8px 4px 0; } .cta-btn { width:100%%; padding:14px 18px; border-radius:14px; font-weight:700; } .btn-primary { background:%s; border-color:%s; } .btn-primary:hover, .btn-primary:focus { filter:brightness(0.95); } .btn-secondary { background:%s; border-color:%s; color:#000; } .btn-secondary:hover { filter:brightness(0.95); } .dataTables_wrapper .dataTables_info, .dataTables_wrapper .dataTables_paginate { font-size:0.98rem; } table.dataTable tbody td, table.dataTable thead th { font-size:1.02rem; } ", hanifa_light, hanifa_dark, hanifa_primary, hanifa_primary, hanifa_accent, hanifa_accent))) ), # ===== Welcome ===== tabPanel( "Welcome", fluidPage( br(), sidebarLayout( sidebarPanel( width = 4, h3("Welcome to HANIFA – PRS Calculator"), div(class="note", HTML("This app computes a polygenic score (PRS) for a single individual.
Choose one of the two workflows:")), tags$hr(), div(class="soft", tags$ul( tags$li(HTML("From Excel: One Excel containing SNP, CHR, BP, Genotype, Weight, RiskAllele.")), tags$li(HTML("Manual Entry: Upload genotype file (TXT/TSV/CSV), then enter rsID/β/risk allele.")) ) ), tags$hr(), div( span(class="kpi","Missing genotypes: --, II, DD"), span(class="kpi","Dosage = copies of risk allele (0/1/2)"), span(class="kpi","Score = Dosage × Weight; PRS = Σ Score") ), tags$hr(), div(class="note","Column names are case‑insensitive in Excel mode.") ), mainPanel( width = 8, div(class="welcome-card", h3("Pick a workflow"), p(class="note","Start by selecting your preferred input method."), fluidRow( column( 6, div(class="soft", h4("From Excel (All‑in‑One)"), p("Upload a single Excel file (XLSX/XLS) with 6 columns: ", code("SNP"), ", ", code("CHR"), ", ", code("BP"), ", ", code("Genotype"), ", ", code("Weight"), ", ", code("RiskAllele"), "."), actionButton("go_excel","Go to Excel workflow", class="btn-primary cta-btn") ) ), column( 6, div(class="soft", h4("Manual SNP Entry"), p("Upload genotype file, then provide ", em("rsID, β, risk allele"), " per SNP."), actionButton("go_manual","Go to Manual workflow", class="btn-secondary cta-btn") ) ) ) ) ) ) ) ), # ===== Excel ===== tabPanel( "From Excel (All-in-One)", fluidPage( br(), sidebarLayout( sidebarPanel( width=4, fileInput("xlsx","Upload Excel (.xlsx / .xls) with columns: SNP, CHR, BP, Genotype, Weight, RiskAllele", accept=c(".xlsx",".xls")), uiOutput("sheet_picker"), actionButton("compute_excel","Compute PRS", class="btn-primary"), tags$hr(), downloadButton("download_xlsx","Download results (XLSX)") ), mainPanel( width=8, h4("Per-SNP results"), DTOutput("table_excel"), tags$hr(), h4("Total PRS"), verbatimTextOutput("prs_excel"), tags$hr(), helpText("Notes: Genotypes treated as missing: --, II, DD. Dosage = copies of risk allele (0/1/2). Score = Dosage × Weight.") ) ) ) ), # ===== Manual ===== tabPanel( "Manual SNP Entry", fluidPage( br(), sidebarLayout( sidebarPanel( width=4, fileInput("geno_file","Upload genotype file (TXT/TSV/CSV):", accept=c(".txt",".tsv",".csv")), helpText("Expected columns (no strict header required): SNP, CHR, BP, Genotype"), tags$hr(), numericInput("snp_count","Number of SNPs:", value=3, min=1, step=1), actionButton("make_inputs","Generate SNP input fields"), tags$hr(), uiOutput("snp_inputs"), actionButton("compute_manual","Compute PRS", class="btn-primary"), tags$hr(), downloadButton("download_manual_xlsx","Download results (XLSX)") ), mainPanel( width=8, h4("Per-SNP results"), DTOutput("table_manual"), tags$hr(), h4("Total PRS"), verbatimTextOutput("prs_manual"), tags$hr(), helpText("Manual mode: Dosage is computed after joining user-provided SNPs/weights/risk-alleles with the uploaded genotype file by rsID.") ) ) ) ) ) # ---------------- Server ---------------- server <- function(input, output, session){ # Use updateNavbarPage for navbarPage containers observeEvent(input$go_excel, { updateNavbarPage(session, "mainnav", selected = "From Excel (All-in-One)") }) observeEvent(input$go_manual, { updateNavbarPage(session, "mainnav", selected = "Manual SNP Entry") }) # Excel mode sheets <- reactive({ req(input$xlsx); readxl::excel_sheets(path = input$xlsx$datapath) }) output$sheet_picker <- renderUI({ req(input$xlsx); selectInput("sheet","Sheet:", choices=sheets(), selected=sheets()[1]) }) df_excel <- reactive({ req(input$xlsx, input$sheet) ext <- tolower(tools::file_ext(input$xlsx$name)) validate(need(ext %in% c("xlsx","xls"), "Please upload an Excel file (.xlsx / .xls).")) # read_excel supports both .xls and .xlsx df <- readxl::read_excel(input$xlsx$datapath, sheet=input$sheet, guess_max = 10000) nm <- std_names(names(df)); names(df) <- nm missing <- setdiff(need_cols_excel, nm) validate(need(length(missing)==0, paste0("Missing required columns: ", paste(missing, collapse=", ")))) df %>% transmute( SNP = as.character(.data[["snp"]]), CHR = as.character(.data[["chr"]]), BP = suppressWarnings(as.double(.data[["bp"]])), Genotype = toupper(as.character(.data[["genotype"]])), Weight = suppressWarnings(as.double(.data[["weight"]])), RiskAllele= toupper(as.character(.data[["riskallele"]])) ) }) results_excel <- eventReactive(input$compute_excel,{ df <- df_excel() validate( need(all(df$RiskAllele %in% c("A","C","G","T")), "RiskAllele must be one of A/C/G/T."), need(all(nchar(df$RiskAllele) == 1), "RiskAllele must be a single nucleotide (A/C/G/T)."), need(all(nchar(df$Genotype)==2 | is_missing_like(df$Genotype)), "Genotype must be like AA/AG/... or --/II/DD.") ) out <- df %>% mutate( SNP = trim_ws(SNP), Genotype = toupper(trim_ws(Genotype)), RiskAllele = toupper(trim_ws(RiskAllele)), Dosage = dosage_vec(Genotype, RiskAllele), Score = Dosage * Weight ) list(table = out, prs = sum(out$Score, na.rm=TRUE)) }, ignoreInit=TRUE) output$table_excel <- renderDT({ req(results_excel()) datatable(results_excel()$table, rownames=FALSE, options=list(pageLength=15, scrollX=TRUE, dom="tp")) }) output$prs_excel <- renderText({ req(results_excel()) sprintf("PRS = %.6f", results_excel()$prs) }) output$download_xlsx <- downloadHandler( filename=function(){ paste0("PRS_results_", format(Sys.time(), "%Y%m%d_%H%M%S"), ".xlsx") }, content=function(file){ req(results_excel()) writexl::write_xlsx( list(per_snp = results_excel()$table, summary = data.frame(PRS = results_excel()$prs)), path = file ) } ) # Manual mode geno_df <- reactive({ req(input$geno_file) ext <- tolower(tools::file_ext(input$geno_file$name)) df <- tryCatch({ if(ext=="csv") readr::read_csv(input$geno_file$datapath, col_names=FALSE, show_col_types=FALSE, progress=FALSE) else readr::read_table(input$geno_file$datapath, col_names=FALSE, show_col_types=FALSE, progress=FALSE) }, error=function(e) NULL) validate(need(!is.null(df),"Could not read the genotype file (CSV/TSV/TXT).")) if(ncol(df)<4){ df <- readr::read_delim(input$geno_file$datapath, delim="\t", col_names=FALSE, show_col_types=FALSE, progress=FALSE) } validate(need(ncol(df)>=4,"File must contain at least 4 columns: SNP, CHR, BP, Genotype.")) names(df) <- c("SNP","CHR","BP","Genotype", paste0("V",5:ncol(df))) df[,1:4] %>% mutate( SNP = as.character(SNP), CHR = as.character(CHR), BP = suppressWarnings(as.double(BP)), Genotype = toupper(as.character(Genotype)) ) }) observeEvent(input$make_inputs,{ output$snp_inputs <- renderUI({ n <- max(1L, as.integer(input$snp_count %||% 1)) tagList(lapply(seq_len(n), function(i){ wellPanel( strong(paste("SNP", i)), textInput(paste0("rs_", i), "rsID:", value = if(i==1) "rs577266494" else ""), numericInput(paste0("w_", i), "Weight (β):", value = NA, step = 0.001), selectInput(paste0("risk_", i), "Risk allele:", choices=c("A","C","G","T"), selected="A") ) })) }) }) results_manual <- eventReactive(input$compute_manual,{ df_g <- geno_df() n <- max(1L, as.integer(input$snp_count %||% 1)) snp_vec <- sapply(seq_len(n), function(i) input[[paste0("rs_", i)]]) w_vec <- sapply(seq_len(n), function(i) input[[paste0("w_", i)]]) risk_vec <- sapply(seq_len(n), function(i) input[[paste0("risk_", i)]]) validate( need(all(nchar(snp_vec)>0), "Please enter all rsIDs."), need(all(!is.na(w_vec)), "Please enter all weights (β)."), need(all(risk_vec %in% c("A","C","G","T")), "Risk alleles must be A/C/G/T.") ) df_in <- tibble(SNP=as.character(snp_vec), Weight=as.numeric(w_vec), RiskAllele=toupper(as.character(risk_vec))) df_join <- df_in %>% left_join( df_g %>% filter(!is.na(SNP), SNP!=".") %>% group_by(SNP) %>% slice(1) %>% ungroup(), by="SNP" ) out <- df_join %>% mutate( SNP = trim_ws(SNP), Genotype = toupper(trim_ws(Genotype)), RiskAllele = toupper(trim_ws(RiskAllele)), Dosage = dosage_vec(Genotype, RiskAllele), Score = Dosage * Weight ) %>% select(SNP, CHR, BP, Genotype, RiskAllele, Weight, Dosage, Score) list(table=out, prs=sum(out$Score, na.rm=TRUE)) }, ignoreInit=TRUE) output$table_manual <- renderDT({ req(results_manual()) datatable(results_manual()$table, rownames=FALSE, options=list(pageLength=15, scrollX=TRUE, dom="tp")) }) output$prs_manual <- renderText({ req(results_manual()) sprintf("PRS = %.6f", results_manual()$prs) }) output$download_manual_xlsx <- downloadHandler( filename=function(){ paste0("PRS_results_manual_", format(Sys.time(), "%Y%m%d_%H%M%S"), ".xlsx") }, content=function(file){ req(results_manual()) writexl::write_xlsx( list(per_snp = results_manual()$table, summary = data.frame(PRS = results_manual()$prs)), path = file ) } ) } shinyApp(ui, server)

Choose one of the two workflows:") ), tags$hr(), div(class="soft", tags$ul( tags$li(HTML("From Excel: One Excel containing SNP, CHR, BP, Genotype, Weight, RiskAllele.")), tags$li(HTML("Manual Entry: Upload genotype file (TXT/TSV/CSV), then manually enter rsID/β/risk allele.")) ) ), tags$hr(), div( span(class="kpi","Genotypes treated as missing: --, II, DD"), br(), br(), span(class="kpi","Dosage = copies of risk allele (0/1/2)"), br(), br(), span(class="kpi","Score = Dosage × Weight; PRS = Σ Score") ), tags$hr(), div(class="note", HTML("Tip: Column names are case-insensitive in Excel mode.")) ), mainPanel( div(class="welcome-card", h3("Pick a workflow"), p(class="note","Start by selecting your preferred input method."), fluidRow( column( width = 6, div(class="soft", h4("From Excel (All‑in‑One)"), p("Upload a single Excel file (XLSX/XLS) with 6 columns:", tags$code("SNP, CHR, BP, Genotype, Weight, RiskAllele")), actionButton("go_excel", "Go to Excel workflow", class = "btn-primary cta-btn") ) ), column( width = 6, div(class="soft", h4("Manual SNP Entry"), p("Upload genotype file, then manually provide ", tags$em("rsID, β, risk allele"), " per SNP."), actionButton("go_manual", "Go to Manual workflow", class = "btn-secondary cta-btn") ) ) ) ) ) ) ) ), # ======== Excel Tab ======== tabPanel( "From Excel (All-in-One)", fluidPage( br(), sidebarLayout( sidebarPanel( fileInput( "xlsx", "Upload Excel (.xlsx / .xls) with columns: SNP, CHR, BP, Genotype, Weight, RiskAllele", accept = c(".xlsx", ".xls") ), uiOutput("sheet_picker"), actionButton("compute_excel", "Compute PRS", class = "btn-primary"), tags$hr(), downloadButton("download_xlsx", "Download results (XLSX)") ), mainPanel( h4("Per-SNP results"), DTOutput("table_excel"), tags$hr(), h4("Total PRS"), verbatimTextOutput("prs_excel"), tags$hr(), helpText("Notes: Genotypes treated as missing: --, II, DD. Dosage = copies of risk allele (0/1/2). Score = Dosage × Weight.") ) ) ) ), # ======== Manual Tab ======== tabPanel( "Manual SNP Entry", fluidPage( br(), sidebarLayout( sidebarPanel( fileInput("geno_file", "Upload genotype file function(input, output, session){ # Welcome navigation buttons observeEvent(input$go_excel, { updateTabsetPanel(session, "mainnav", selected = "From Excel (All-in-One)") }) input$sheet) ext <- tools::file_ext(input$xlsx$name) validate(need(tolower(ext) %in% c("xlsx","xls"), "Please upload an Excel file (.xlsx / .xls).")) df <- read_xlsx(input$xlsx$datapath, sheet = input$sheet, guess_max = 10000) nm_std <- std_names(names(df)) names(df) <- nm_std missing <- setdiff(need_cols_excel, nm_std) validate(need(length(missing) == 0, paste0("Missing required columns: ", paste(missing, collapse = ", ")))) df %>% transmute( SNP = as.character(.data[["snp"]]), CHR = as.character(.data[["chr"]]), BP = suppressWarnings(as.double(.data[["bp"]])), Genotype = toupper(as.character(.data[["genotype"]])), Weight = suppressWarnings(as.double(.data[["weight"]])), RiskAllele = toupper(as.character(.data[["riskallele"]])) ) }) results_excel <- eventReactive(input$compute_excel, { df <- df_excel() validate( need(all(df$RiskAllele %in% c("A","C","G","T")), "RiskAllele must be A/C/G/T."), need(all(nchar(df$Genotype) == 2 | is_missing_like(df$Genotype)), "Genotype must be like AA/AG/... or a missing placeholder (--/II/DD).") ) out <- df %>% mutate( SNP = trim_ws(SNP), Genotype = toupper(trim_ws(Genotype)), RiskAllele = toupper(trim_ws(RiskAllele)), Dosage = dosage_vec(Genotype, RiskAllele), Score = Dosage * Weight ) list( table = out, prs = sum(out$Score, na.rm = TRUE) ) }, ignoreInit = TRUE) output$table_excel <- renderDT({ req(results_excel()) datatable(results_excel()$table, rownames = FALSE, options = list(pageLength = 15, scrollX = TRUE, dom = "tp")) }) output$prs_excel <- renderText({ req(results_excel()) sprintf("PRS = %.6f", results_excel()$prs) }) output$download_xlsx <- downloadHandler( filename = function(){ paste0("PRS_results_", format(Sys.time(), "%Y%m%d_%H%M%S"), ".xlsx") }, content = function(file){ req(results_excel()) writexl::write_xlsx( list( per_snp = results_excel()$table, summary = data.frame(PRS = results_excel()$prs) ), path = file ) } ) # ====== Manual mode ====== geno_df <- reactive({ req(input$geno_file) ext <- tolower(tools::file_ext(input$geno_file$name)) df <- tryCatch({ if (ext == "csv") { readr::read_csv(input$geno_file$datapath, col_names = FALSE, show_col_types = FALSE, progress = FALSE) } else { readr::read_table(input$geno_file$datapath, col_names = FALSE, show_col_types = FALSE, progress = FALSE) } }, error = function(e) NULL) validate(need(!is.null(df), "Could not read the genotype file.")) if (ncol(df) < 4) { df <- readr::read_delim(input$geno_file$datapath, delim = "\t", col_names = FALSE, show_col_types = FALSE, progress = FALSE) } validate(need(ncol(df) >= 4, "File must contain at least 4 columns: SNP, CHR, BP, Genotype.")) df <- df[,1:4] names(df) <- c("SNP","CHR","BP","Genotype") df %>% mutate( SNP = as.character(SNP), CHR = as.character(CHR), BP = suppressWarnings(as.double(BP)), Genotype = toupper(as.character(Genotype)) ) }) observeEvent(input$make_inputs, { output$snp_inputs <- renderUI({ n <- input$snp_count %||% 1 n <- max(1L, as.integer(n)) tagList(lapply(seq_len(n), function(i) { wellPanel( strong(paste("SNP", i)), textInput(paste0("rs_", i), "rsID:", value = if (i == 1) "rs577266494" else ""), numericInput(paste0("w_", i), "Weight (β):", value = NA, step = 0.001), selectInput(paste0("risk_", i), "Risk allele:", choices = c("A","C","G","T"), selected = "A") ) })) }) }) results_manual <- eventReactive(input$compute_manual, { df_g <- geno_df() n <- input$snp_count %||% 1 n <- max(1L, as.integer(n)) snp_vec <- sapply(seq_len(n), function(i) input[[paste0("rs_", i)]]) w_vec <- sapply(seq_len(n), function(i) input[[paste0("w_", i)]]) risk_vec <- sapply(seq_len(n), function(i) input[[paste0("risk_", i)]]) validate( need(all(nchar(snp_vec) > 0), "Please enter all rsIDs."), need(all(!is.na(w_vec)), "Please enter all weights (β)."), need(all(risk_vec %in% c("A","C","G","T")), "Risk alleles must be A/C/G/T.") ) df_in <- tibble( SNP = as.character(snp_vec), Weight = as.numeric(w_vec), RiskAllele = toupper(as.character(risk_vec)) ) df_join <- df_in %>% left_join( df_g %>% filter(!is.na(SNP), SNP != ".") %>% group_by(SNP) %>% slice(1) %>% ungroup(), by = "SNP" ) out <- df_join %>% mutate( SNP = trim_ws(SNP), Genotype = toupper(trim_ws(Genotype)), RiskAllele = toupper(trim_ws(RiskAllele)), Dosage = dosage_vec(Genotype, RiskAllele), Score = Dosage * Weight ) %>% select(SNP, CHR, BP, Genotype, RiskAllele, Weight, Dosage, Score) list(table = out, prs = sum(out$Score, na.rm = TRUE)) }, ignoreInit = TRUE) output$table_manual <- renderDT({ req(results_manual()) datatable(results_manual()$table, rownames = FALSE, options = list(pageLength = 15, scrollX = TRUE, dom = "tp")) }) output$prs_manual <- renderText({ req(results_manual()) sprintf("PRS = %.6f", results_manual()$prs) }) output$download_manual_xlsx <- downloadHandler( filename = function() paste0("PRS_results_manual_", format(Sys.time(), "%Y%m%d_%H%M%S"), ".xlsx"), content = function(file){ req(results_manual()) writexl::write_xlsx( list( per_snp = results_manual()$table, summary = data.frame(PRS = results_manual()$prs) ), path = file ) } ) } shinyApp(ui, server)

name: OLD/utils/ensure.R
OLD/utils/get_app_from_app_url.R
OLD/utils/launch_app.R
OLD/utils/package_manager.R
content:
# capture the current working directory
# set the package search path to the app specific library
appwd <- getwd()
applibpath <- file.path(appwd, "library")

message("library path:\n", paste("...", applibpath, "\n"))
message("working path:\n", paste("...", appwd, "\n"))
message("interactive R session:\n", paste("...", interactive(), "\n"))

# Load functions to ensure software dependencies and check the internet
source("utils/ensure.R")

# Create app/library if it doesn't exist (e.g. first run)
# Initialize RInno
if (!dir.exists(applibpath)) {
  pb <- winProgressBar(
    title = "Starting RInno ...",
    label = "Initializing ...")

  dir.create(applibpath)
  init_pkgs <- c("jsonlite")

  for (i in seq_along(init_pkgs)) {
    setWinProgressBar(pb, value = i / (length(init_pkgs) + 1),
      label = sprintf("Loading package - %s", init_pkgs[i]))
    pkg <- list.files(appwd, paste0(init_pkgs[i], ".*zip$"), full.names = TRUE, recursive = TRUE)
    install.packages(pkgs = pkg, lib = applibpath, repos = NULL, type = "win.binary")
  }
  close(pb)
}

# Add app/library to R's library search path
.libPaths(c(applibpath, .libPaths()))

# Read the application config
library("jsonlite", character.only = TRUE)
config <- jsonlite::fromJSON(file.path(appwd, "utils/config.cfg"))

# Package dependency list
pkgs_loc <- config$pkgs$pkgs_loc; pkgs_names <- config$pkgs$pkgs_names

# Provide some initial status updates
pb <- winProgressBar(
  title = sprintf("Starting %s ...", config$appname),
  label = "Initializing ...")

# Use tryCatch to display error messages in config$logging$filename
appexit_msg <- tryCatch({

  # ensure all package dependencies are installed
  message("ensuring packages: ", paste(pkgs_names, collapse = ", "))
  setWinProgressBar(pb, 0, label = "Ensuring package dependencies ...")

  ensure(pkgs_loc)

  for (i in seq_along(pkgs_names)) {
    setWinProgressBar(pb,
      value = i / (length(pkgs_names) + 1),
      label = sprintf("Loading package - %s", pkgs_names[i]))

    library(pkgs_names[i], character.only = TRUE)
  }

  # If an app repository has been provided, install the app from there
  if (config$app_repo[[1]] != "none") {
    source("utils/get_app_from_app_url.R")
  }

  setWinProgressBar(pb, 1.00, label = "Starting application")
  close(pb)

  # Start the app
  source(file.path(appwd, "utils/launch_app.R"))

  "application terminated normally"
},
error = function(e) {
  msg <- sprintf("Startup failed with error(s):\n\n%s", e$message)
  tcltk::tk_messageBox(
    type = "ok",
    message = msg,
    icon = "error")

  msg
},
finally = {
  close(pb)
})

message(appexit_msg)
